@startuml
title SECCAP - Diagrama de despliegue logico
top to bottom direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

node "Cliente institucional" as Cliente {
  artifact "Navegador web\nChrome / Firefox / Edge" as Browser
}

node "Servidor Web / Reverse Proxy" as Web {
  artifact "Frontend SPA estatico\nReact + TypeScript + Vite" as Frontend
  artifact "TLS / HTTPS" as TLS
}

node "Servidor de aplicacion" as App {
  artifact "Backend Proxy\nNode.js 22 + Express 5\nTypeScript" as Backend
  artifact "Middlewares\nAuth / RBAC / CORS / Rate Limit / Logging" as Middlewares
  artifact "Health endpoint\nGET /health" as Health
}

database "PostgreSQL local" as Postgres {
  artifact "usuarios" as T1
  artifact "roles y permisos" as T2
  artifact "sesiones" as T3
  artifact "auditoria" as T4
  artifact "configuracion" as T5
  artifact "catalogo_cache" as T6
}

cloud "API Institucional RRHH" as Api {
  artifact "REST/JSON Read-Only" as ApiData
}

Browser --> TLS : HTTPS
TLS --> Frontend
Frontend --> Backend : HTTPS / REST JSON
Backend --> Postgres : TCP / SQL parametrizado
Backend --> Api : HTTPS / REST JSON
Health --> Postgres
Health --> Api

note right of Backend
  El backend concentra:
  - autenticacion
  - autorizacion por rol
  - validacion de filtros
  - integracion con API
  - poda de campos
  - auditoria
end note

note bottom of Cliente
  No existe acceso directo
  desde el navegador a la API externa.
end note

note bottom of Postgres
  La tabla de auditoria debe ser inmutable.
  No se almacenan datos maestros del personal.
end note

@enduml

